Oct 1 2009 	Had High Expectations and Omni Exceeded Them	I was in San Francisco for a conference and needed a room for 3 nights. I used a third party booker (starts with Price and ends with Line) and got an amazing deal on the Omni. I was very happy, because Omni is one of the highest ranked hotels in San Francisco. Now I know why.The Omni is located in the Financial District, which means it’s a fairly short distance from touristy spots such as Union Square, Embarcadero, Chinatown and Pier 39. It also seems relatively safe. There are plenty of restaurants nearby, both dinner style and “grab something quick” like Jamba Juice and Subway. Upon arrival, I realized I’d forgotten my phone charger. The front desk clerk, seeing that I was a little upset, offered to check housekeeping for a loaner. Five minute later she came back with a charger and said I could use it for the duration of my stay. Her helpfulness plus the cheery, happy, glad-to-be-at-work vibe given off by the rest of the employees in lovely lobby got my stay off to a good start.I had to wait a half hour for my room, which was no big deal since I’d arrived earlier than 3. One of the most cheerful porters I’ve ever encountered took my bags and held them while I ran to get some lunch. When the room was ready, I was surprised at how large it was – especially considering I’d booked third party. Omni didn’t discriminate and attempt to put me in the broom closet, which to be honest, has happened only once at a different hotel where I’d booked through the bargain booker.The room had a very long hallway – so long I could run laps back and forth. The bathroom was huge, the bed was big and comfy (as usual for Omni) and the room had a sofa, desk, chest of drawers and two flat screen TVs which could be adjusted so that I could view them from about any point in the room. The room didn't have a lot of light, but it didn't bother me, and the view was of people working in the offices in the building next door, which wasn't scenic, but slightly entertaining. As for the noise level, the only noise I ever heard coming from another room was a shower in a nearby bathroom. Overall, the room was very quiet.So the location was great, service was outstanding and the room exceeded my expectations.Room service prices were very, very expensive, but that’s to be expected. However, I was able to order from the bar at the restaurant downstairs (Bob’s) and take the food back up to the room. That cut the costs down tremendously and the cobb salad I ordered was excellent. I’d love to go back to San Francisco for a longer stay at The Omni, and hopefully, with family. I read they have a kids’ suite with bunk beds attached to a king suite. Final Note: Omni's Internet was free to members. To be a member, you just sign up on their website or when you get to the hotel. It's free and you get free Internet access. The room I was in wasn't wireless, but they provided a cord and I didn't have any major issues getting or staying online.	
Sep 29 2009 	Not perfect But a Good Stay and at a Reasonable Cost	My wife and I vacation in the Bay Area frequently. Given the number of top-notch hotels in The City, we usually pick and choose a new one each trip. This time we landed the Omni on a discount website for about $125 per night. Given all of the good reviews on Trip Advisor, we were excited to give it a try.The location of the hotel is better for business than leisure. While I like the Embarcadero area for its proximity to BART and the ferry building, we found ourselves constantly trudging up-hill toward Union Square or Pacific Heights for dinner and sightseeing. We do a lot of walking when staying in the City anyway, so the additional few blocks (all uphill) was a bit of overkill. In short, we largely prefer staying in Union Square and probably will skip the Omni because of its location on our next stay.All other aspects of the hotel were well above-average -- our check in went smoothly. The staff was attentive and pleasant. Our room was clean and comfortable, although very average in size and accommodations. The lobby area is attractive and the hotel is a very good mix of luxury and value. Overall, we found the Omni to be an excellent value and a good choice for a home base while staying in San Francisco. Our only complaint was the location, but for a business trip it would be perfect.	
