Sep 8 2009 	Great hotel and staff! We would definitely stay here again!	We stayed here over Labor Day Weekend and everything was fantastic! We called ahead to find out more about the BART system and the concierge, Tara was very helpful. Mass Transit is the way to go in San Fran! Of course you must take advantage of the infamous Trolley cars (NOTE: pick up the trolley in the morning one block down from the hotel. You can buy tickets on-board. Otherwise, you will wait nearly an hour to get on the trolley at Powell Street or at Ghiradelli Square. Don't forget the MUNI. It is great too!! We took the MUNI to Haight/Ashbury and walked to Golden Gate park. The BART is fantastic to go to and from the airport. It cost $16.20 round-trip from SFO to Montgomery Street. The hotel is 5 blocks from the BART station. Don't waste your money on a $50 cab fare one-way! Anyway, we were greeted by Justin who check us in. We did not have any issues with check-in as some other people had indicated in other reviews. Justin was very friendly and cordial. He recommended a restaurant close by (Tadich Grille) so we had a quick dinner. Justin called some tour companies for us as we wanted to see Alcatraz. NOTE: If you plan on seeing Alcatraz PLEASE book your tickets in advance. I had been to SF ten years ago and never had a problem getting tickets to Alcatraz. I was told SF is so popular now that Alcatraz is sometimes booked for 3 weeks! We ended up getting tickets but it was by pure luck!! If you want to book tickets in advance, the Alcatraz ticket agent told me to book on the official Alcatraz website NOT a broker. We saw people turned away because their tickets from a &quot;broker&quot; weren't valid. All of the staff were very friendly and knowledgable at the Omni. We booked a 21-day advance so we got the best rate. Albeit, the rooms were a little small but VERY nice. The bathrooms are very nice with granite countertops and VERY clean as well. The lobby was nice with complimentary coffee. The hotel is a short walk or trolley ride to Chinatown and North Beach (Little Italy). Please check out Calzones in North Beach. It's a great Italian restaurant. It sounds like a pizza place but it's not. They have great food! Albeit, I don't think you can go wrong at any of the Italian restaurants. They all have outdoor cafe style seating. The Omni is in the financial district so there isn't alot of nightlife (which we liked). It was very quiet at night. If you want a hotel closer to bars or entertainment you might want to find something closer to Union Square. Overall, we really enjoyed our stay at the Omni very much and would definitely stay here again!!	
