Aug 6 2009 	Deserves its high ranking for SF!	In spite of the fact that we were staying over a very busy weekend (the front-desk staff mentioned that the hotel was completely booked), everyone, from doormen to cleaning staff we happened to pass in the hall, was friendly, professional, and efficient. Our room met every expectation: it was exceptionally clean, spacious (for a hotel in the city), tastefully decorated, and had thoughtful little touches here and there – like the glass jar in the bathroom with sealed packets of cotton swabs and cotton balls, in case you’d forgotten to pack your own. And even though the hotel was full, the room was exactly of the kind I’d requested in my Select Guest profile. The room was also well soundproofed; once in a while we’d hear a door opening or closing in the hallway, but mostly there was silence, broken only by the occasional, lovely sound of the cable car bell as it passed up California St.  The hotel is near the Financial District, which means that the area is quieter at night and on weekends. So if you’re looking for something at the center of the city’s action, then this is probably not for you. However, it was only a short distance away from the hubbub of the high-density tourist areas: about 10 minutes walking to Union Square &amp; shopping, around 20-30 minutes to the SFMOMA and Asian Art Museums, and also has easy access to streetcars, buses, and the BART subway system.  Hopefully they’ll equip all rooms with wifi at some point. For now, it’s only available on a few floors (with higher-priced rooms), and upon arrival we had some inconvenient fumbling with cables and such before we got the internet running. But even with this little exception, I’d love to stay here on my next visit to San Francisco!	
