Jun 6 2009 	Great customer care at a wonderful location	I just finished my first stay in an Omni Hotel, and I am very impressed. This San Francisco hotel is marvelously located because you can easily walk to Chinatown, North Beach (the Italian part of town), the Westfield mall, Curran theatre, the Embarcadero &amp; Ferry Building, etc. The trolley runs by the front door. And of course, there is a Starbucks every half block and a Jamba Juice nearby so you can get coffee as well as an oatmeal breakfast.The beds are very comfortable, the bathroom counters spacious, and bathrobes are provided. If you ask for a wake-up call, a real person calls you in the morning. The front desk is efficient and friendly. The doormen and valets are the same. The fitness center is well-equipped with Precor equipment including 5 treadmills, 2 recumbent bicycles, and several ellipticals.The key to having a really great stay is to join the Omni Select Guest program. Then you get internet free, and they deliver the NYT or WSJ in the morning along with coffee and juice. The downsides to this hotel are (1) parking with tax is about $54 per night, but that's pretty much a standard SF hotel rate. (2) The furnishings in the room are not top notch. The wall decor is pretty sparse, the Sharp flat panel TV has the slowest channel changer I've seen in a long time, and the nightstands are flimsy. (3) The rooms only have wired internet access. Wireless is only available in the lobby.	
