Dec 30 2008 	Omni - Great SF Hotel	Conveniently located within easy walking distance from North Beach, Chinatown, the Embacadero, museums, and great shopping, the Omni is a four star hotel with five star service. The lobby is all marble and highly polished gleam, and the friendly, accommodating staff insure a wonderful, pampered stay. From the doormen to the housekeepers, these hospitality pros understand the meaning of the concept of service. When I asked where I could buy a Chronicle newspaper nearby, one was delivered to my room. The concierge handled all the paperwork for my rental car arrangements, including delivery to the hotel at no extra cost. After a message was briefly delayed, I went to the desk to ask for an explanation of what I had done wrong with the phone in the room, and the desk staff immediately apologized for &quot;our mistake&quot;. There's no question that I was the one who made the mistake, but how refreshing to find employees who see their job as making me feel at ease. Service staff count on tips for a significant part of their income, but I never got the feeling that anyone had their hand out for money. Their hands were always reaching to assist me with a bag, or a door, or a taxi. The food is a cut above most hotel fare as well. I can't imagine staying anywhere else in San Francisco.	
Dec 30 2008 	Best Vacation in Years	From the moment my cab pulled up and I was warmly greeted, I had the idea that this was going to be a very special vacation. Check-in was easy, no fuss, friendly, and efficient. Our room was spacious, welcoming, efficient, and warm, all at the same time. Because we were tired, we ordered dinner in the room. This and breakfast every day in our room were tasty, well-presented, and took very little time to arrive. The robes were warm, towels plentiful, and the shower comfortable for our romantic weekend. The bed was large, yet cozy, the comforter snuggly, and the mattress great for sore backs. Throughout the stay, the staff treated us warmly, and in a dignified manner. There were always little treats available in the lobby, including fruit, cookies, cider, and coffee. We plan to return whenever possible, and make it a Christmas tradition. The location is perfect for shopping and touring.	
Dec 23 2008 	Loved the Omni...well it was pretty good anyway	I booked through a conference website for $160/night including tax. The location is good, near to Union Square, China Town and the Coit Tower and on a tram line. I was initially not impressed since everything seemed expensive (e.g. $6 bottle of water in the room - I used the tap). Also I didn't bother with breakfast at $20 for continental and $26 for cooked (perfectly good Chinese deli next door).You just need to join &quot;Select Guests&quot; and not only do you get free internet access (not Wi-fi yet though) but you are also treated to a free 2 morning drinks (e.g. posh tea and grapefruit juice) and a &quot;turndown&quot; service (which I'd never heard of): you come home to find relaxing music on and ice in the wine cooler and a chocolate mint!Any problems I had were dealt with well (free internet help line) and overall a positive experience. I don't usually like these rather souless posh city hotels, but this was pretty good after early reservations.	
